</code><code>#include &lt;cursor.h&gt;
</code><code>#include "screen.h"</code></pre>
<p>The gscreen -is accessed from the 'devmouse.c',
therefore it needs to be visible outside this file.
I was wondering how that happens, but of course it's like this.</p>
<p>I provide some pin mappings here to configure the communication with the display.</p>
<p>I also provide the display width/height here,
because I also need to provide the driving voltage.
It's weird because the 'devinfo'
provides the dimensions but not the driving voltage.
Meh, I guess somebody just messed something up there.</p>
